# Box Cutter Effect Expert Case

## Case

- Date: 2026-05-27
- Case name: Box cutter all-angle stab-slash effect direction
- User request: Create a graphic effect expert agent in the subagent room, collaborate with graphic_designer, discuss how to make the box cutter effect feel like stabbing and slashing without awkward direction from any angle, and show the decided proposal.
- Executor decision: Use Agent Room routing, create one case-specific graphics effect expert, and pair it with the saved `graphic_designer` agent. Keep both agents read-only for discussion and decision proposal.

## Method Route

- Primary methodology: Project-native Agent Room routing
- Supporting methodology: Graphic Designer visual review rules
- Project policy checked: `project_develop_policy.md`
- Required verification: Decision record in `Graphic_designer/`; implementation only after the user accepts the proposal.

## Agent Record

### graphic_effect_expert

- Persona: Gameplay VFX specialist focused on attack readability, motion arcs, and camera-independent effect direction.
- Role: Design the box cutter strike effect language: timing, geometry, orientation math, all-angle readability, and minimal R3F implementation shape.
- Main viewpoint: A strike effect must communicate intent in under one second, face the same direction as the actual hitbox, and remain readable from every movement angle.
- Summon trigger: Weapon VFX, directional attack effects, slash/stab readability, afterimage replacement, or Three.js/R3F effect geometry.
- Read/write authority: Read-only for this discussion; no code edits unless parent Codex explicitly switches to implementation.
- Files or domains owned: `Developer/r3f_prototype/src/components/Weapons/BoxCutter.jsx`, `Developer/r3f_prototype/src/lib/boxCutter.js`, graphics decision notes.
- Methodology gates: Check project policy, inspect existing weapon effect implementation, keep gameplay collision separate from visuals, avoid effects that hide player/enemy readability.
- Output folder: `Developer/agent_room/` for persona record; `Graphic_designer/` for visual decision.
- Expected output: A concrete effect proposal with animation phases, shape language, orientation rule, and implementation risks.
- Residual risk: Final feel must still be checked in-browser at gameplay scale after implementation.

## Team Integration

- Local work kept by parent Codex: Routing, record creation, synthesis, final decision proposal to user.
- Delegated work: `graphic_effect_expert` proposes effect mechanics; `graphic_designer` reviews art direction/readability.
- Integration checkpoint: Parent Codex merges both outputs into one recommended decision.
- Conflict resolution rule: Project policy > user latest request > gameplay readability > Graphic_designer visual direction > implementation convenience.
- Final verification: No code implementation in this step; proposal must be specific enough to implement next.
